        "title": "Metasploit ",
        "content": "## 1. Installation on Kali Linux (Easiest)\n\nMetasploit is native to Kali. You don't \"install\" it as much as you \"initialize\" it.\n\n| Step | Command | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **1. Update** | `sudo apt update` | Fetches the latest package lists. |\n| **2. Install** | `sudo apt install metasploit-framework` | Ensures the latest version is installed. |\n| **3. Setup DB** | `msfdb init` | **Crucial:** Initializes the database for faster searching. |\n| **4. Launch** | `msfconsole` | Opens the Metasploit command interface. |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Installation on Windows\n\nInstalling on Windows is tricky because **Windows Defender will try to delete it** immediately.\n\n### **Pre-installation Requirement:**\n\n* You **must** disable Real-time Protection in Windows Security or add an exclusion folder for the installation path.\n\n### **Steps:**\n\n1. **Download:** Go to the [Metasploit Nightly Installers](https://github.com/rapid7/metasploit-framework/wiki/Nightly-Installers).\n2. **Download the `.msi` file:** Look for the Windows 64-bit installer.\n3. **Run Installer:** Follow the wizard.\n4. **Run via CMD:** Open a **Command Prompt as Administrator** and type:\n```cmd\nmsfconsole\n\n```\n\n\n\n---\n\n## 3. Installation on macOS\n\nFor Mac, the most stable way to install and manage Metasploit is using **Homebrew**.\n\n| Step | Command | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **1. Homebrew** | `/bin/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)\"` | Installs Homebrew if you don't have it. |\n| **2. Install MSF** | `brew install --cask metasploit` | Downloads and installs the framework. |\n| **3. Verify** | `msfconsole` | Launches the framework from your terminal. |\n\n---\n\n## üõ†Ô∏è Global \"First Run\" Checklist\n\nRegardless of which OS you use, run these commands inside `msfconsole` to ensure your system is ready:\n\n* **`db_status`**: Ensure it says \"Connected to msf.\" If not, searching for exploits will be very slow.\n* **`msfupdate`**: Run this frequently to get the newest 2025 exploits.\n* **`version`**: Check your current build.\n\n---\n"
