        "title": "Nikto Cheat Sheet",
        "content": "## **Nikto Cheat Sheet**\n\n### **1. What is Nikto?**\n- Open-source web server vulnerability scanner\n- Tests for:\n  - Dangerous files/programs\n  - Outdated server versions\n  - Server misconfigurations\n  - Security issues in web applications\n- Supports anti-IDS evasion techniques\n- Provides both security and information-gathering checks\n\n### **2. Installation & Setup**\n\n**Clone Repository:**\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/sullo/nikto\n```\n\n**Navigate to Program Directory:**\n```bash\ncd nikto/program\n```\n\n**Switch to Stable Branch (Optional):**\n```bash\ngit checkout nikto-2.5.0\n```\n\n### **3. Updating Nikto**\n```bash\ncd /path/to/nikto\ngit pull\n```\n\n### **4. Running Nikto**\n\n**Method 1: Using Shebang (Make executable first):**\n```bash\nchmod +x nikto.pl\n./nikto.pl -h http://target.com\n```\n\n**Method 2: Using Perl directly:**\n```bash\nperl nikto.pl -h http://target.com\n```\n\n### **5. Essential Scan Commands**\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `nikto -h http://target.com` | Basic scan |\n| `nikto -h http://target.com -port 8080` | Scan specific port |\n| `nikto -h http://target.com -ssl` | Force SSL scan |\n| `nikto -h http://target.com -Tuning 489` | Custom tuning options |\n| `nikto -h http://target.com -output scan.txt` | Save results to file |\n\n### **6. Command Line Flags Quick Reference**\n\n**Basic Options:**\n- `-h` : Target host\n- `-p` : Port (default: 80)\n- `-ssl` : Use SSL\n- `-id user:pass` : HTTP authentication\n- `-Format` : Output format (txt, html, xml, csv, nbe)\n\n**Scan Tuning (`-Tuning`):**\n- `1` : Interesting files\n- `2` : Misconfigurations\n- `3` : Information disclosure\n- `4` : Injection attacks\n- `9` : SQL Injection\n- `0` : File upload issues\n- `a` : Authentication bypass\n- `b` : Software identification\n\n**Display Options (`-Display`):**\n- `V` : Verbose output\n- `E` : Show HTTP errors\n- `D` : Debug mode\n- `P` : Show progress\n\n### **7. Practical Examples**\n\n**Basic Scanning:**\n```bash\n# Standard scan\nnikto -h 192.168.1.100\n\n# Scan with specific tuning\nnikto -h example.com -Tuning 489\n\n# Non-interactive scan\nnikto -h target.com -nointeractive\n\n# SSL scan on port 443\nnikto -h https://target.com -ssl\n```\n\n**Advanced Scanning:**\n```bash\n# Mutate scan for enumeration\nnikto -h target.com -mutate 3\n\n# Scan with evasion\nnikto -h target.com -evasion 167\n\n# Scan with timeout\nnikto -h target.com -maxtime 1h\n```\n\n### **8. Using with Proxy**\n\n**Basic Proxy Setup:**\n```bash\nnikto -h target.com -useproxy -proxyhost 127.0.0.1 -proxyport 8080\n```\n\n**With Authentication:**\n```bash\nnikto -h target.com -useproxy -proxyhost proxy.com -proxyport 8080 -proxyuser user -proxypass pass\n```\n\n### **9. Nikto2 Key Features**\n- ‚úÖ SSL/TLS support\n- ‚úÖ Multiple output formats (HTML, XML, CSV, NBE)\n- ‚úÖ HTTP proxy support\n- ‚úÖ IDS evasion techniques\n- ‚úÖ Database-driven vulnerability checks\n- ‚úÖ Plugin architecture\n- ‚úÖ Virtual host scanning\n- ‚úÖ Automatic updates\n- ‚úÖ Authentication support (Basic, NTLM)\n- ‚úÖ False positive reduction\n- ‚úÖ Customizable templates\n\n### **10. Output Examples**\n\n**Save in Different Formats:**\n```bash\nnikto -h target.com -output results.html -Format htm\nnikto -h target.com -output results.xml -Format xml\nnikto -h target.com -output results.csv -Format csv\n```\n\n### **11. Tips & Best Practices**\n1. **Start with basic scan**, then add tuning options\n2. **Use `-nointeractive`** for automated scans\n3. **Combine with proxy** (Burp/ZAP) for manual testing\n4. **Check updates regularly**: `nikto -update`\n5. **Use `-maxtime`** for time-constrained engagements\n6. **Save all outputs** for documentation\n7. **Verify critical findings** manually\n\n### **Document Information**\n- **Last Updated**: 12/02/2024\n- **Author**: Arr0way\n- **Version**: Nikto 2.5.0+\n- **License**: Open Source (GPL)\n\n---\n"
