        "title": " Recon-ng",
        "content": "---\n\n## ‚úÖ Step 1: Install Recon-ng\n\n### On Kali Linux (recommended):\n```bash\nsudo apt update && sudo apt install recon-ng\n```\n\n### Or from source (if not in Kali):\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/lanmaster53/recon-ng.git\ncd recon-ng\npip3 install -r REQUIREMENTS\n./recon-ng\n```\n\n> üí° You‚Äôll see the prompt: `[*] Version <X.X.X>`\n\n---\n\n## ‚úÖ Step 2: Start Recon-ng & Create a Workspace\n\nWorkspaces isolate data (like projects). Always use one!\n\n```bash\nrecon-ng\n```\n\nInside Recon-ng:\n```bash\n# List existing workspaces\nworkspaces list\n\n# Create a new workspace (e.g., for target: example.com)\nworkspaces create example_com\n\n# Select (activate) it\nworkspaces select example_com\n```\n\n> üî∏ You‚Äôre now in the `example_com` workspace. All data will be saved here.\n\n---\n\n## ‚úÖ Step 3: Discover All Available Modules\n\n### List all modules:\n```bash\nshow modules\n```\n\nYou‚Äôll see output like:\n```\nrecon/domains-hosts/hackertarget\nrecon/domains-hosts/ssl_san\nrecon/domains-contacts/hunter\ndiscovery/info_disclosure/interesting_files\nreporting/csv\n...\n```\n\n### Filter modules (e.g., find all for \"domains ‚Üí hosts\"):\n```bash\nshow modules | grep \"domains-hosts\"\n```\n\nOr use built-in search:\n```bash\nmarketplace search hackertarget\n```\n\n---\n\n## ‚úÖ Step 4: Understand Module Categories\n\n| Category | Purpose |\n|--------|--------|\n| `recon/` | Passive info gathering (e.g., emails, hosts, domains) |\n| `discovery/` | Find files, misconfigs, disclosures |\n| `import/` | Load external data (Nmap, CSV, etc.) |\n| `reporting/` | Export results (CSV, HTML, JSON) |\n\n---\n\n## ‚úÖ Step 5: Run a Module ‚Äì Full Example\n\n### üéØ Goal: Find subdomains of `example.com`\n\n#### Step 5.1: Load a module\n```bash\nuse recon/domains-hosts/hackertarget\n```\n\n> ‚úÖ This module uses [HackerTarget API](https://hackertarget.com) ‚Äî **no API key needed**.\n\n#### Step 5.2: View module info & options\n```bash\ninfo\n```\nShows description and required options.\n\n```bash\nshow options\n```\nOutput:\n```\nName    Current Value  Required  Description\n----    -------------  --------  -----------\nSOURCE  example.com    yes       source input (see 'info' for supported formats)\n```\n\n#### Step 5.3: Set the target\n```bash\nset SOURCE example.com\n```\n\n#### Step 5.4: Run the module\n```bash\nrun\n```\n\n> ‚è±Ô∏è Wait a few seconds. Results auto-save to the database.\n\n#### Step 5.5: View results\n```bash\nshow hosts\n```\n\nOutput:\n```\n+----+-------------------+-------------+\n| id | host              | ip          |\n+----+-------------------+-------------+\n| 1  | www.example.com   | 93.184.216.34|\n| 2  | blog.example.com  | 93.184.216.34|\n+----+-------------------+-------------+\n```\n\n---\n\n## ‚úÖ Step 6: Chain Multiple Modules\n\n### Find more hosts via SSL certificates:\n```bash\nuse recon/domains-hosts/ssl_san\nset SOURCE example.com\nrun\nshow hosts\n```\n\n### Find emails (requires Hunter.io API):\n```bash\nkeys add hunter_api YOUR_HUNTER_KEY\nuse recon/domains-contacts/hunter\nset SOURCE example.com\nrun\nshow contacts\n```\n\n---\n\n## ‚úÖ Step 7: Export Results\n\n### Save hosts as CSV:\n```bash\nuse reporting/csv\nset TABLE hosts\nset FILENAME /tmp/example_hosts.csv\nrun\n```\n\n### Generate HTML report:\n```bash\nuse reporting/html\nset CREATOR \"Your Name\"\nset CUSTOMER \"Example Corp\"\nrun\n```\n> Report saved in `~/.recon-ng/workspaces/example_com/`\n\n---\n\n## ‚úÖ Step 8: Use Marketplace (Install Extra Modules)\n\nSome modules aren't installed by default.\n\n```bash\n# Refresh marketplace\nmarketplace refresh\n\n# Search for Shodan module\nmarketplace search shodan\n\n# Install it\nmarketplace install recon/domains-hosts/shodan_hostname\n\n# Now use it\nuse recon/domains-hosts/shodan_hostname\nkeys add shodan_api YOUR_KEY\nset SOURCE example.com\nrun\n```\n\n---\n\n## ‚úÖ Step 9: Exit & Reuse Later\n\n```bash\nexit\n```\n\nLater, restart and reload your workspace:\n```bash\nrecon-ng\nworkspaces select example_com\nshow hosts  # your data is still there!\n```\n\n---\n\n## üîÅ Quick Reference: Full Workflow Cheat Sheet\n\n```bash\nrecon-ng\nworkspaces create target\nworkspaces select target\n\nuse recon/domains-hosts/hackertarget\nset SOURCE target.com\nrun\n\nuse recon/domains-hosts/ssl_san\nset SOURCE target.com\nrun\n\nshow hosts\nshow domains\n\nuse reporting/csv\nset TABLE hosts\nset FILENAME /tmp/target.csv\nrun\n\nexit\n```\n\n---"
